What is the structure of your dataset?¶

The dataset has 183412 observations(rows) and 16 variables(columns) that represent bike users in FordGoBike which is a bike-sharing system covering the greater San Francisco Bay area in the year 2019.

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

The main features of interest in this dataset are user_type, member_gender, member_birth_year, duration_sec, start_time and end_time.

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

The duration, day, month and year would help in comparing different variables such as user_type, gender and even bike_share_for_all_trips

The days of the week had more trip than weekends, weekends had a close distribution, but it's clear that the peak of the ride is on Thursdays.

Age had some problems with outliers but most riders were between 25 to 50 years. Log scale was needed to produce the correct result due to the large number of points.

Talk about some of the relationships you observed in this part of the investigation. Were there features that strengthened each other in terms of looking at your feature(s) of interest?¶

Looking at member gender and user type across day of the ride, we see a pattern for all gender types. They ride more during the weekday than weekend. Further inspection of the user type of these genders, we saw that most where subscribers.

Ride Duration in different hours taking into account the user type, we saw that both user types ride more during rush or peak hours of the day.

Ride duartion of each day for difrfrent memeber gender, by adding the 'member gender' in the equetion we can now observe the average trip duration of each gender in diffrent days

Were there any interesting or surprising interactions between features?¶

It was not clear at first but after bulding a pointplot we can see that 'other" gender has much higher ride duration than male and female genders and customer has higher trip duration than subscriber in avarage.

Conclusions¶

From the analysis, we discovered that as age increases the ride duration decreases which implies than the younger ones tend to last longer in rides than the elderly ones. It was also seen that most of the rides took place during the rush hours of the day. Further more customers has high ride duration than subscribers which totally makes sense as they would love to enjoy the ride to the fullest while their payment last.
